# ============================================================================
# CAMPUSFINDS FRONTEND - ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES FOR VITE
# ============================================================================
# 
# CRITICAL: All variables must have VITE_ prefix to be accessible in Vite 
# projects via import.meta.env.<VARIABLE_NAME>
# 
# This file defines development defaults. For production (Vercel), set these
# variables in Vercel's Project Settings > Environment Variables.
#
# ============================================================================
# VITE_API_URL - Backend API Base URL (REQUIRED)
# ============================================================================
#
# PURPOSE:
#   - Dynamically routes all frontend API calls to the correct backend server
#   - Enables local development and production deployments without code changes
#   - Prevents CORS errors by ensuring frontend calls match backend origin
#
# REQUIRED IN:
#   - Local development (.env.local or .env)
#   - Vercel production environment (Project Settings > Environment Variables)
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DEVELOPMENT SETUP (Local Machine)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. For local development with backend on localhost:5000:
#    VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000
#
# 2. For local development with remote backend (e.g., testing Vercel locally):
#    VITE_API_URL=https://campusfinds-major.onrender.com
#
# 3. Copy this file to .env.local and uncomment below:
#    $ cp .env.example .env.local
#
# Then edit .env.local with your local backend URL.
# 
# NOTE: .env.local is Git-ignored and specific to your machine
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PRODUCTION SETUP (Vercel Cloud Deployment)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Go to: https://vercel.com/dashboard
# 2. Select your CampusFinds project > Settings > Environment Variables
# 3. Create a new environment variable:
#    Name:  VITE_API_URL
#    Value: https://campusfinds-major.onrender.com (or your backend URL)
#    Environment: Production
# 4. Click "Save"
# 5. Redeploy your Vercel project:
#    - Option A: Git push to trigger automatic redeploy
#    - Option B: Manual redeploy via Vercel Dashboard
#
# VERCEL REBUILD REQUIRED:
#   Environment variables are baked into the build. After saving, you MUST
#   redeploy for changes to take effect in the production build.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CORS & FETCH COMPATIBILITY
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# ✅ LOCAL DEV: Vite proxy (vite.config.js) routes /api to localhost:5000
#    Result: fetch('/api/users/login') → http://localhost:5000/api/users/login
#
# ✅ VERCEL PROD: VITE_API_URL prepended to all calls
#    Result: fetch(`${VITE_API_URL}/api/users/login`) 
#           → https://campusfinds-major.onrender.com/api/users/login
#
# ✅ CORS HEADERS: Backend must allow:
#    - Origin: https://campusfinds.vercel.app (Vercel domain)
#    - Methods: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE
#    - Headers: Content-Type, Authorization
#    See backend CORS configuration in server.js
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CODE USAGE PATTERNS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Pattern 1 - Axios (Recommended for Services):
#   import api from '@/api';  // Pre-configured with VITE_API_URL
#   api.get('/lost-items').then(r => r.data)
#
# Pattern 2 - Fetch with Explicit BaseURL:
#   const baseUrl = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL || '';
#   fetch(`${baseUrl}/api/users/login`, { ... })
#
# Pattern 3 - Relative URLs (Dev Only):
#   fetch('/api/items')  // Routed via Vite proxy in dev
#   // !!! FAILS IN PRODUCTION - avoid this pattern !!!
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# ❌ "Failed to fetch" in Vercel:
#    1. Check VITE_API_URL is set in Vercel Project Settings
#    2. Check backend is running and accessible at that URL
#    3. Check backend CORS allows origin: https://campusfinds.vercel.app
#    4. Verify no relative URLs in code (must use ${baseUrl}/api/...)
#    5. Redeploy Vercel after changing env vars
#
# ❌ Localhost works but Vercel fails:
#    1. .env.local is correct for dev but ignored by Vercel
#    2. Vercel uses only env vars in Project Settings
#    3. Set VITE_API_URL in Vercel dashboard, not in files
#
# ❌ Relative URLs broken in production:
#    1. Relative URLs only work with Vite proxy (dev only)
#    2. Production: Always use `${import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL}/api/...`
#    3. Or use imported axios instance: `api.get('/endpoint')`
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLE VALUES BY DEPLOYMENT MODE
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# | Environment      | Backend URL (Render)                     | VITE_API_URL Value                  |
# |------------------|------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------|
# | Local Dev        | http://localhost:5000                    | http://localhost:5000               |
# | Vercel Preview   | https://campusfinds-major.onrender.com   | https://campusfinds-major.onrender.com |
# | Vercel Production| https://campusfinds-major.onrender.com   | https://campusfinds-major.onrender.com |
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DEFAULT VALUE (For Local Development)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# This is the default used during npm run dev (local Vite dev server)
# For your machine's setup, ensure /backend is running on port 5000
#
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000
